%% TrustyAI Explainability - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Dashboard
    participant Sidecar as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>PVC/MinIO/MariaDB
    participant InfServer as KServe/ModelMesh<br/>Inference Server (gRPC)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over Client, Storage: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Ingestion
        participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Serving
        ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>80/TCP HTTP, No Auth
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference payload<br/>PVC (local) / MinIO (443/HTTPS) / MariaDB (3306/MySQL)
    end

    rect rgb(220, 255, 220)
        Note over Client, Storage: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Payload Ingestion
        participant KServe as KServe Inference Logger
        participant Knative as Knative Eventing
        KServe->>Knative: CloudEvent<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request/response<br/>80/TCP HTTP
        Knative->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent delivery<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Store inference payload<br/>PVC/MinIO/MariaDB
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 220)
        Note over Client, Prometheus: Flow 3: Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
        Client->>Sidecar: POST /metrics/group/fairness/dir<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS, Bearer Token
        Sidecar->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Read inference data
        Storage-->>TrustyAI: Inference records
        TrustyAI-->>Sidecar: Metric result (JSON)
        Sidecar-->>Client: Metric result

        Note over TrustyAI, Prometheus: Scheduled metrics (every 5s default)
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: PrometheusScheduler computes metrics
        Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, Bearer Token (SA)
        TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir gauges
    end

    rect rgb(255, 220, 220)
        Note over Client, InfServer: Flow 4: Explainability (LIME/SHAP) - Disabled in RHOAI
        Client->>Sidecar: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
        Sidecar->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
        TrustyAI->>InfServer: ModelInfer RPC<br/>gRPC (configurable port)
        InfServer-->>TrustyAI: Inference results
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute LIME explanation
        TrustyAI-->>Sidecar: Explanation response (JSON)
        Sidecar-->>Client: Explanation response
    end
